name: integer_i64_binary64_first_lost_negative
description: |
  This is -(2^53 + 1), the first negative integer by magnitude that does not
  survive conversion to binary64 and back. Round-to-nearest maps it to -2^53,
  checking that signed conversion loses precision symmetrically.
format: hex
decode-as: i64-le
pair:
  - with: ../u64/binary64-first-lost-integer.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i64"
  - "binary64"
  - "float-roundtrip"
  - "negative"
  - "precision-loss"
  - "boundary"
---
ff ff ff ff ff ff df ff   # -9007199254740993 (-(2^53 + 1))
